dpram_ctrl shows the interfaces provided by the DPRAM men_lx_z149 driver.
When men_lx_z149 is loaded, the /dev/dpram device node is created.

The following file operations are available:
	- open, close and mmap
	- ioctl to get the DPRAM physical address and size
	- ioctl to send an interrupt to the NIOS
	- ioctl to read the interrupt from the NIOS
	- ioctl to reset the interrupt from the NIOS

This driver does not support mutli-threaded accesses.
